<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-86-0576 </DOCNO><TEXT>Reaction of the co-ordinatively unsaturated carbene thiochelate anion[Cr{C(O/sup -/)=C(SR/sup 1/)SR/sup 2/}(CO)/sub 3/(THF)] with variousligands has been investigated. The P-donor ligand, P(OMe)/sub 2/(0SiMe/sub3/) substitutes THF to yield, after alkylation, chiral tricarbonyl complexes.The ligands S=CN(H)CH/sub 2/CH/sub 2/NH and S=CSCH/sub 2/CH/sub 2/S causedisplacement of THF and the carbene thioether chelate, leading to pentacarbonylthione complexes. The reaction with S=CSCH/sub 2/CH/sub 2/S a thermolabileintermediate, gives rise to the dithiocarbene complex [Cr(CO)/sub 5/CSCH/sub2/CH/sub 2/S] and affords [Cr(CO)/sub 4/(CNBu/sup t/)CSCH/sub 2/CH/sub2/S] on reaction with CNBu/sup t/. Due to decreased reactivity of theco-ordinated thiocarbonyl group and the presence of the metal, novelreactions could be effected at other centres on the thione ligand inthe complex [Cr(CO)/sub 5/S=CSCH/sub 2/CH/sub 2/S]. Deprotonation followedby alkylation gives rise to ylid complex [Cr(CO)/sub 5/{S=CS(Et)=CHCH/sub2/S}]. Consecutive deprotonation, addition of CS/sub 2/ and alkylationyield a co-ordinated thioaldehyde [Cr(CO)/sub 5/{S=CHCH=C(SEt)/sub 2/}].Irradiation of [Fe(CO)/sub 5/] in the presence of [Cr(CO)/sub 5/S=CSCH/sub2/CH/sub 2/S] results in formation of the cluster compounds [(CO)/sub3/FeSCSCH/sub 2/CH/sub 2/SFe(CO)/sub 3/-{mu}S/sup 1/,C,S] (Fe-Fe), XVII,and [{Fe(CO)/sub 3/}/sub 3/({mu}/sub 3/-CSCH/sub 2/CH/sub 2/S-{mu}C,S)({mu}/sub3/-S)] (2Fe-Fe), XVI, as well as [{Fe(CO)/sub 3/}/sub 3/({mu}/sub 3/-S/sub2/)] (2Fe-Fe) and [(CO)/sub 3/FeSCH/sub 2/CH/sub 2/SFe(CO)/sub 3/] (Fe-Fe)to employ 2-lithiobenzothiazole as an {alpha}-thio carbanion, analogousto 2-lithio-1,3-dithiane, the conversions led to the carbene complex[Cr{CN(Et)C/sub 6/H/sub 4/-S-o}(CO)/sub 5/], XI. When 2-lithio-benzothiazolereacts with [Cr(CO)/sub 6/] in THF-solution, the carbene complex [Cr{C(OEt)C=NC/sub6/H/sub 4/-S-o}(CO)/sub 5/], XII, is obtained after alkylation. (AbstractTruncated)</TEXT></DOC>